{{Italic title}} {{taxobox |name = ''Delosperma sutherlandii'' |image = Delosperma sutherlandii 3.JPG |regnum = [[Plant]]ae |unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]] |unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]] |unranked_ordo = [[Core eudicots]] |ordo = [[Caryophyllales]] |familia = [[Aizoaceae]] |genus = ''[[Delosperma]]'' |species = '''''D. sutherlandii''''' |binomial = ''Delosperma sutherlandii'' |binomial_authority = <!-- (Hook.f.) L.Bolus --> |}}
'''''Delosperma sutherlandii''''' is a dwarf [[perennial plant]], native to [[South Africa]]. It forms a dense lawn with abundant, long-lasting flowering. It will reach sizes of 60&nbsp;cm in diameter and approximately 10–15&nbsp;cm tall, with possibly the largest flowers of its type.<ref name=mon>{{cite web |title=Sutherland Hardy Iceplant |url=http://www.monrovia.com/plant-catalog/plants/1644/sutherland-hardy-iceplant.php |publisher=Monrovia.com |accessdate=6 January 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130127173309/http://www.monrovia.com/plant-catalog/plants/1644/sutherland-hardy-iceplant.php |archivedate=27 January 2013 |df= }}</ref>
==Cultivation and uses== It can be cultivated in a wide range of areas with a [[Mediterranean climate]].
