{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox film | name = Kadavul | image = | image_size = | caption = | director = [[Velu Prabhakaran]] | producer = H.Anraaj | writer = Velu Prabhakaran | starring = {{ubl|[[Velu Prabhakaran]]| |[[C. Arunpandian|Arun Pandian]]|[[Manivannan]]|[[Mansoor Ali Khan (actor)|Mansoor Ali Khan]]|[[Roja (actress)|Roja]]|Rahul|Nandhini|V. Gopalakrishnan|Karikalan|NagaKannan|[[Roopa Sri]]}} | music = [[Ilaiyaraaja]] | cinematography = Velu Prabhakaran | editing = Nandamuri Haribabu | distributor = | studio = Deccan Pictures PVT. LTD. | released = {{Film date|df=y|1997|12|05}} | runtime = 130 minutes | country = India | language = Tamil }}
'''Kadavul''' ({{lang-en|God}}) is a [[Tamil films of 1997|1997]] [[Tamil language|Tamil]] anti-theist film directed by [[Velu Prabhakaran]]. The film features Velu Prabhakaran, [[Manivannan]], [[C. Arunpandian|Arun Pandiyan]], [[Mansoor Ali Khan (actor)|Mansoor Ali Khan]] and [[Roja (actress)|Roja]] in lead roles. The film, produced by H. Anraaj, had musical score by [[Ilaiyaraaja]] and was released on 5 December 1997. Despite having controversial themes, the film was well received.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spicyonion.com/movie/kadavul/|title=Kadavul (1997) Tamil Movie|accessdate=2013-04-21|publisher=spicyonion.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indolink.com/tamil/cinema/Specials/97/Oct/a-z/atoz-3.htm|title=A-Z (III) - INDOlink|accessdate=2013-04-21|publisher=indolink.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2009/06/26/stories/2009062650351600.htm|title=Grill Mill|author= S. R. Ashok Kumar|date=2009-06-26|accessdate=2013-04-21|publisher=hindu.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/july-07-03/19-07-07-velu-prabhakaran.html|title= ‘Manaivikku nadanda thirumanam’|date=2007-07-19|accessdate=2013-04-21|publisher=behindwoods.com}}</ref> The film was dubbed and released in Telugu as ''Shakti''.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oZ0Kyt1Mmtk</ref>
==Plot==
Parvathi ([[Roja (actress)|Roja]]), a young woman, is a goddess believer while her father (V. Gopalakrishnan) is the priest of a temple. After a quarrel between two castes during a Hindu festival, the temple was closed off. Five years later, the temple reopens.
Muthu (Rahul) and Thenmozhi (Nandhini) are in love but they are not of the same caste. Velusamy (Karikalan), Thenmozhi's uncle, finds out their love and forces her to marry him.
K. Shanmugam ([[Mansoor Ali Khan (actor)|Mansoor Ali Khan]]), a corrupt [[Member of the Legislative Assembly (India)|MLA]], kills a girl and blames Thamizharasan ([[C. Arunpandian|Arun Pandian]]). Thamizharasan fights against injustice and is a revolutionary. Angry, Thamizharasan tries to kill him but fails and eventually steals his money. In the process, Thamizharasan is injured and the prostitute Shenbagam (Rupasri) takes care of him.
Rajapandi (Velu Prabhakaran), an atheist, propagates the non-existence of God. One day, he saves Parvathi from her uncle K. Shanmugam and gets married to her accidentally. Soon, Rajapandi gets beaten by the devotees. In anger, Rajapandi challenges God to become a human and understand the humans, and God ([[Manivannan]]) appears as a human.
